Product Description

Dhokra or the Bell Metal craft dates back its origin to pre-historic time of Indus Valley Civilization. Tribal craftsmen from Madhya Pradesh Chattisgarh Orissa West Bengal and parts of Andhra Pradesh have carried this tradition since then.

Dhokra work has been inspired by the rich folk culture of India. Dhokra products are in great demand in India as well as outside for its simplicity and enchanting fold motifs.

This dhokra depicts a Ganpati made of brass. The frame used for the work is also hand made by the artisan.

Product Festures:

  • Dimensions: 13.5 inches long X 11.5 inches wide X 0.5 inches deep
  • Weight:500 gms
  • Material:Brass and wooden frame
  • Origin:Bastar Madhya Pradesh
